<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-17033] MessagingServiceTest listenOptionalSecureConnection and listenRequiredSecureConnection fail sporadically</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-17033</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This popped up in a recent CircleCI run: &lt;a href=&quot;https://app.circleci.com/pipelines/github/maedhroz/cassandra/351/workflows/f8dbf599-df72-4982-8a12-a72a5b8ddd3b/jobs/2195&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://app.circleci.com/pipelines/github/maedhroz/cassandra/351/workflows/f8dbf599-df72-4982-8a12-a72a5b8ddd3b/jobs/2195&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I was able to reproduce it locally on trunk as well in a single run, although it happens perhaps once per 3-4 runs of the MessagingServiceTest suite. It looks like we open the sockets in an InboundSockets container, await on the future that returns, and then assert that all those sockets are open. It&#8217;s not clear to me yet why this assertion fails sporadically, or what state changes exactly are racing.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
