                            <comment id="17438976" author="dcapwell" created="Thu, 4 Nov 2021 23:07:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;found the issue; 2 bugs&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) test doesn&apos;t wait on the future...&lt;br/&gt;
2) future combiner isn&apos;t working, need to use the non-netty methods and works just fine then.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17438977" author="dcapwell" created="Thu, 4 Nov 2021 23:08:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;the issue looks localized to trunk as the future refactor is what looks to have caused this&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17440818" author="dcapwell" created="Mon, 8 Nov 2021 23:45:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;the issue was that the future returned from open would return and call a callback async; this callback sets the state that isOpen depends on (causing the flaky behavior). The patch fixes this so that all state is updated before the future open returns gets completed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
